title: Oshkosh shocks top-ranked Whitewater
text:
(0) Comments 
A strong defensive effort ruled the day for UW-Oshkosh as it stunned top-ranked UW-Whitewater, 10-7, on Saturday afternoon in Oshkosh, stopping the Warhawks' winning streak at 36 games. 
Greg Rand connected on a 41-yard field goal with 10 minutes, 45 seconds remaining in the game to put the 15th-ranked Titans (4-1, 2-0 WIAC) ahead. 
After both teams were forced to punt, the Warhawks (4-1, 1-1) got the ball and drove to the Oshkosh 27-yard line where they stalled. 
Lake Bachar attempted a game-tying field goal from 44 yards out for Whitewater, but it was blocked by Brandon Lloyd. 
Whitewater's usually high-powered offense was held to just 221 yards and was 3 of 11 (27%) in third-down conversions. 
The Titans last beat the Warhawks in 2012 at Forrest Perkins Stadium in Whitewater. 
"I remember when we won in 2012 and I was in the room with the reporters," Oshkosh coach Patt Cerroni said. "I said it's going to take us five years to get back to this point. We're at three, so I'm really proud of that. 
"The will to win today for us, that's what got us through." 
UW-Platteville 30, UW-Stevens Point 27: Jack Eddy's fourth touchdown pass of the day, a 4-yard connection to Russell Martin with 6:14 remaining, carried the host Pioneers (4-1, 1-1 WIAC) over the Pointers (3-2, 1-1). 
Eddy threw for 375 yards for Platteville, which overcame four turnovers in its homecoming game. 
Quinn Buschbacher caught nine passes for 127 yards and a touchdown, and Patrick Sheehan also hauled in nine passes for 115 yards and a score for the Pioneers. 
Kyle Larson had two touchdown passes, but he also threw two interceptions for Point. 
UW-River Falls 10, UW-Eau Claire 7: Ryan Kusilek's 20-yard field goal with 4:57 remaining in the second quarter proved to be the winner as the Falcons (3-2, 2-0 WIAC) picked up a road victory over the Blugolds (0-5, 0-2). 
The Falcons were led by their pass defense, which produced three sacks for a loss of 17 yards and three interceptions. 
UW-La Crosse 28, UW-Stout 21: The host Eagles (2-3, 1-1 WIAC) got three touchdown passes from John Tackett against the Blue Devils (1-4, 0-2). 
Stout pulled within seven points on Adolfo Pacheco's touchdown with 2:40 remaining, but the Blue Devils were unable to recover the ensuing onside kick.
